<import-ordering>

<title>Import Organization Rules</title>

<rules>
- Group imports into three categories in this order: external packages, internal modules, relative imports
- Place external packages (from node_modules) first
- Place internal modules (absolute imports from project) second
- Place relative imports (starting with ./ or ../) last
- Add exactly one blank line between each import group
- Sort imports alphabetically within each group
- Keep imports from the same package together
</rules>

<examples>
<example type="good">
```typescript
// External packages
import React from 'react';
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import axios from 'axios';
import lodash from 'lodash';

// Internal modules
import { ApiClient } from '@/services/api';
import { UserService } from '@/services/user';
import { authConfig } from '@/config/auth';
import { logger } from '@/utils/logger';

// Relative imports
import { Button } from './components/Button';
import { Header } from './components/Header';
import { formatDate } from '../utils/date';
import styles from './styles.module.css';
```
</example>
